item.title: Our Story
item.dc:creator: hello@stnsvn.com
item.content:encoded:
We're Mike and Brittni, a creative couple from Vancouver, Canada – husband and wife, best friends and business partners. After a few years pushing paper in the public sector, we felt a growing restlessness and discontent in our professional lives. Where did our work go once it disappeared into the ether – did it make a difference, did we matter? Outgrowing our habitat of windowless offices, we knew we needed to make a change. So we did!

We’ve chosen instead to build something of our own, where the outcomes of our hard work are tangible and rewarding. Designing minimalist WordPress themes for passionate entrepreneurs allows us to give back and enable others to create something of their own. We aim to craft themes that’ll help creatives stand out among a sea of sameness and get noticed; this is the driving force behind our work and the reason we spend countless hours perfecting every detail. Our goal has always been to make great web design accessible, not just to those who can afford it, but to anyone who has a vision and the guts to make it happen.

The demise of the sidebar has resulted in some great new design possibilities and we're jumping in feet first. Starting with this purposely minimalist blog design. We're not lazy, we swear, we just love big, huge photos smack in the middle of a white page. Don't you? Especially when it's your lovely work and thoughtfully crafted words locking eyes with readers. Now, we're not bloggers (not lately anyway), so we won't go on and on about our love for a great single column blog. Isn't it refreshing? One, single column of beautiful content surrounded by airy whitespace. The demise of the sidebar has resulted in some great new design possibilities and we're jumping in feet first. Starting with this purposely minimalist blog design. We're not lazy, we swear, we just love big, huge photos smack in the middle of a white page. Don't you? Especially when it's your lovely work and thoughtfully crafted words locking eyes with readers. Now, we're not bloggers (not lately anyway), so we won't go on and on about our love for a great single column blog. Instead we'll simply add in some dummy text to help you visualize and move on to the next item on our to-do list. How about another photo for good measure as well? item.title: An Optional Blog Sidebar Layout
item.dc:creator: hello@stnsvn.com
item.content:encoded: Sometimes you just want to mix it up, and now with our optional sidebar layout you can do just that. Choose to add a sidebar to the entire blog, or just to specific posts - the choice is really up to you! A fully widgetized sidebar is the perfect place for a signup form, some social media links, archives, search bar and more. Choice is a beautiful thing, isn't it?
